James and Lily live off the grid, raising their young daughter in a cocoon of

friends that show up at their door for protection and community. The unexpected 
reunion--abundant with revelry and remembrances, generously enhanced by organic 
wine and weed--is quickly undermined by the slights of the past, the spark of 
lingering flirtations and the threat of a locally grown new world order.
